    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL RIDE OPTIMIZED SUSPENSION (IROS)</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsection id="S03013" svcsectype="prodspec" division="truck" date="12/01/2005">
        <title>INTERNATIONAL RIDE OPTIMIZED SUSPENSION (IROS)</title>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>3200</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>3300</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>CE Bus</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>CE 200</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>CE 300</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>FE Bus</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>RE Bus</truckmodel>
                <ucodegroup/>

                <ucode>14TBJ</ucode>
                <ucode>14TBG</ucode>
                <ucode>14TBH</ucode>
                <ucode>14TBT</ucode>
                <ucode>14WAW</ucode>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <lev1>
                    <para>The air ride suspension is the ultimate in smooth, shock and vibration-free ride with a preset
                        constant frame height.
                    </para>
                    <para>The air springs on the air ride suspension take the place of steel springs, which means there
                        is no inter-leaf friction to overcome; thereby, minimum road shock is transferred to the frame,
                        cargo and driver (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0301301">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                        and
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0301302">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>The air ride system dump feature is only available on the 3200 Model. See Section 9 of
                                this service manual for description and operation of the 14899 Dump Option for the 3200
                                model.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                    <para>The air ride suspension adjusts to load changes automatically, providing a low rate suspension
                        with a light or no load condition, and a higher rate suspension with heavier loads. The major
                        components of the air suspension system, used on single axles are shown in the Figure below.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f0301301" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic filename="../figg03/G0301301.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                                 scalefitheight="312px"/>
                        <caption>Figure 1. Air Suspension (CE, FE, RE)</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. FORWARD CROSSMEMBER</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. FRAME RAIL</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. REAR AXLE</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. AXLE STOPS</callout1>
                            <callout1>5. U-BOLTS</callout1>
                            <callout1>6. REAR CROSSMEMBER</callout1>
                            <callout1>7. AIR SPRING MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                            <callout1>8. AIR SPRING</callout1>
                            <callout1>9. LOWER U-BOLT MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                            <callout1>10. TAPERED LEAF SPRING</callout1>
                            <callout1>11. TAPERED LEAF SPRING FRONT MOUNTING BUSHING ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                            <callout1>12. SUSPENSION MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="f0301302" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic filename="../figg03/G0301302.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                                 scalefitheight="272px"/>
                        <caption>Figure 2. IROS Suspension (RE Shown)</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. SHOCK ABSORBER</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. HEIGHT CONTROL VALVE</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. HEIGHT CONTROL ROD</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. AIR SPRING</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </lev1>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
